dataIdInfo.idAbs:
2010 U.S. Census blockgroup boundaries with 2010 population by race and 2000 population by race. 2000 population data was summarized from 2000 ESRI block point data which was modified by MARC staff. (blocks_2000_modified.shp) A small number of block points were moved within their blocks to be in residential areas and outside of zero-population 2010 blockgroups so that the 2000 to 2010 population change is not misinterpreted.

Fields starting with 'P2" contain 2010 population data that is compared with the 2000 population data. The "P2" data shows both race and Hispanic origin, treating Hispanic origin as a racial subtype. As a result, the sum of the racial categories equals the total population. The P1 data treats race and Hispanic origin as two distinct demographic categories. "P1" and "P2" fields describe the entire population. "P3" and "P4" fields describe the voting age population, age 18 and over.

2000 Census population by race is only included for Leavenworth, Johnson, Miami and Wyandotte Counties in Kansas and Cass, Clay, Jackson, Platte and Ray Counties in Missouri.
